a proper setup for viewing ANSI art in xterm.

includes dos437, a BDF pixel-for-pixel translation of the DOS 437 codepage
font.

to use, convert the BDF font to a PCF font (if necessary) and then install it:
	- bdftopcf dos437.bdf > fonts/dos437.pcf
	- sudo cp fonts/dos437.pcf /usr/X11R6/lib/X11/fonts/misc/
	- cd /usr/X11R6/lib/X11/fonts/misc/; sudo mkfontdir

run ansiterm:
	- sh ansiterm.sh

for tiling window managers, make sure the resulting xterm window is exactly 80
characters wide.

cat some ANSI art:
	- cat acid-100/lorez/GO-EAST.ANS
